OOC: Alrighty!

IC:

Alarm wasn't on yet. Good. Exit. Need to find it. Dang!

Balistica found herself in a part she did not recognize. In fact, she
recognized no part of the base at all. They all looked the same
gunmetal color, functional, devoid of any spark. This one, however,
looked different. There were computers, lots of them, as well as a
door that clearly indicated warning signs, but warnings of what.
Against any common sense, Balistica entered. What she found surprised her.

There was a Maximal, his affiliation symbol clearly visible on his
chestplate, lying down on a table. Wires ran from him to the
computers... or was it the other way around? Nonetheless, those Preds
were obviously going to do something with him... if they hadn't
started yet.

She walked up to him and tried to wake him up. Unsuccessful, she
furiously grabbed the wires and ripped them off.

Balistica: Come on, by Primus' spark, wake up, just wake up!
